    <div class="content-header">
      <h1>Why Choose Cotton?</h1>
      <p>Cotton is one of the world's most beloved natural fibers — and for good reason. Here's why choosing 100% cotton products makes a difference.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-body">
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>
          <svg class="h2-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#7a9e7e" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20"/><path d="M2 12h20"/><path d="m4.93 4.93 14.14 14.14"/><path d="m19.07 4.93-14.14 14.14"/></svg>
          Breathability
        </h2>
        <p>Cotton fibers have a natural twist that creates tiny air pockets, allowing air to circulate freely. This makes cotton clothing naturally cooling in summer and insulating in winter. Unlike synthetic fabrics that trap heat and moisture, cotton lets your skin breathe.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>
          <svg class="h2-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#7a9e7e" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M8 14s1.5 2 4 2 4-2 4-2"/><line x1="9" y1="9" x2="9.01" y2="9"/><line x1="15" y1="9" x2="15.01" y2="9"/></svg>
          Gentle on Skin
        </h2>
        <p>100% cotton is naturally hypoallergenic and unlikely to cause skin irritation. It's free from the chemicals and synthetic materials that can trigger allergies, eczema, or contact dermatitis. This is why cotton is the go-to choice for baby clothing and sensitive skin care.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>
          <svg class="h2-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#7a9e7e" stroke-width="2"><path d="M14 9V5a3 3 0 0 0-3-3l-4 9v11h11.28a2 2 0 0 0 2-1.7l1.38-9a2 2 0 0 0-2-2.3zM7 22H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-7a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h3"/></svg>
          Durability
        </h2>
        <p>Here's a surprising fact: cotton gets <em>stronger</em> when wet. Unlike many synthetics that weaken with washing, cotton fibers actually become more durable over time. A well-made cotton garment can last for years — even decades — with proper care.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>
          <svg class="h2-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#7a9e7e" stroke-width="2"><path d="M7 19a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h6a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-7H7v7z"/><path d="M5 12a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v2a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2h-2"/><path d="M10 12v-2a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h0a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v2"/></svg>
          Sustainability
        </h2>
        <p>100% cotton is fully biodegradable. When a cotton product reaches the end of its life, it breaks down naturally without leaving microplastics behind. Organic cotton takes this further by using less water, no synthetic pesticides, and promoting healthier soil.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>
          <svg class="h2-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#7a9e7e" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2a10 10 0 1 0 10 10"/><path d="M12 2v10l7-7"/></svg>
          Temperature Regulation
        </h2>
        <p>Cotton absorbs up to 27 times its own weight in water, wicking moisture away from your skin. This natural moisture management keeps you dry and comfortable in hot weather, while still providing warmth when it's cold.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>
          <svg class="h2-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#7a9e7e" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 6h18"/><path d="M19 6v14a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V6"/><path d="M8 6V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h4a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v2"/></svg>
          Easy Care
        </h2>
        <p>Cotton is machine washable, can handle high heat, and actually gets softer with each wash. It's one of the easiest natural fibers to care for — no special detergents or delicate cycles required.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>What About Cotton Blends?</h2>
        <p>Not all cotton products are 100% cotton — and that's okay. Blends like 80% cotton/20% polyester offer the softness of cotton with added stretch and wrinkle resistance. The key is knowing what you're getting. That's why we list the exact cotton percentage for every product on CottonFinder.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Organic vs Conventional Cotton</h2>
        <p>Organic cotton is grown without synthetic pesticides or fertilizers, using methods that have a lower environmental impact. It's typically softer and safer for sensitive skin. Look for GOTS (Global Organic Textile Standard) certification for the highest standards.</p>
      </section>
